sVnews
p4
VVisakha Music and Dance Academy featured a concert of Hindi and Telugu ghazals at Kalabharathi inVisakhapatnam recently. Nihal Konduri of Hyderabad who's equally at home rendering Hindustani and Carnatic versions of classical and all varieties of devotional, light and film music, treated the audience to some of the fine renditions. Harjeet, Sunil Rao and Arun lent support on tabla, harmonium and guitar, local artiste Seetharamayya played the keyboard.Evocatively surfacing the specific intonation of rendering ghazals with fervour, he delighted all alike in the auditorium.He chose to sing six numbers in Telugu like Andamaina Gulaabi, Chedumingina Koila, Yenthatheeyani bhandhamo, Idemi mounaraagamo and Chirugaaliki Ooge mungurule, scripted by Sarada Ashokavardhan, Oleti Paarvateesam, B. Madhusoodana and others. He also rendered four in Hindi, Hungamahai Kyu, Chupke Chupke, Rudadein Mohabhat and Ranj Ki Jab.Most of them (Telugu and Hindi) were set to music by V. Muralikrishna, in ragas like Pahadi, Yaman and Bhageswari.
